<br>
Perhaps I am somewhat ignorant on the topic.  But I don't consider a Mob Boss who orders a hit to be necessarily evil.  I don't consider a Palestinian killing an Israeli an evil person.  I don't consider Castro to necessarily be an evil person, regardless of how many deaths he has on his hands.  Stalin wasn't evil, just ruthless.  Was every single one of the soldiers who fired weapons at Tianamen Square evil?  Many of these people's above actions I would have no problem calling evil.  But that doesn't make them an evil person, anymore then someone going to church and thinking that NOW they are a good person.  Even Anton LeVay (R.I.P) IMO wasn't truly evil, most of his teachings taught men to be indulgent, rather then destructive.  And as heinous as the act you prevented from happening was, the impression I get is that it was based on racial hatred.  To act upon racial hatred is a weakness as I see it, versus someone evil who would have shot them even though there was no animosity other then the fact that they were people.  In fact, if that person was truly evil they would have shot you first so they wouldn't have had to worry about interference with their enjoyment.  Perhaps our disagreeing all boils down to degrees Brog, and differentiating between evil deeds and evil people.<br>
<br>
Your first point was pretty good I'll admit, nice to see someone who can effectively debate a point without just having to call me a dumb poo-poo head, and I hadn't looked at it the way you explained it.  <br>
<br>
It sounds like you're being kinda hard on yourself thinking you were evil at the time Brog.  All of us (well excepting Pali because she's perfect) do, have done, and will do things that we will not be proud of.  Perhaps you acted in the past in ways that you consider evil Brog, and perhaps they were.  But that doesn't make YOU an evil person, it just means you made some poor choices.  And learned from them, taking at least a lesson in what not to do with you, and a resolve not to let things deteriorate like that again.  Doesn't sound like the work of someone evil B. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/upalibadgerclaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pali Badgerclaw</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber Druid Tank</span><br> <font color=#778899>(1/21/02 5:48:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.animfactory.com/animations/animals/dolphins/dolphin_face1_md_blk.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why do we care, and what is evil</span><hr size=1> Ugle I have never said I was perfect... get off the high horse already... Just because I told you I would delete anymore rants on my news board does not say I am perfect.... You bashed alot of us without KNOWING us.... That is where im coming from... I have never once called you a dumb Poo poo head or anything I just said basically that you were ignorant to what you were typing... Maybe perhaps you were being misunderstood... But it would seem that you already have your formed opinion on me so it wont matter anymore what Ihave to say...... <br>
